  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Prospective study enrolling patients with cerebral palsy and with subluxation of the hips &gt;
      40% and acetabular dysplasia. The patients will be stratified according the degree of
      subluxation and age. The treatment protocol is composed by femur variation osteotomy and
      periacetabular osteotomy. Patients will be divided in two groups according the type of bone
      graft used at periacetabular osteotomy (autologous or ceramic).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
